nagame (libngm)

This library aims to provide a basic abstraction layer (or API) to handle drawing on your screen through the legacy DRM API
(preferably from a fresh TTY without any graphical server running, since DRM master may not be available).
For now, it only uses the CPU and a dumb frame buffer, tearing can happen, no vblank yet and buffer flipping.

Main functionalities as is:
- create a ngm_root that acts as the main container for the abstraction
- from this container you have access to informations about your display screen (for now the first found, no multiscreen), such as width, height, refresh rate
- you also have access to a framebuffer mapped to a dumb framebuffer that the kernel will use to draw

this framebuffer is the main entrypoint for you to play with drawing on your screen

See examples in test.c file, for now a very basic usage of this library.
